20 Minute Chicken Burrito Bowls
By :Chop Secrets
Print Recipe
Votes: 190
Rating: 4.35
Rate this recipe!
Course Dinner
Difficulty Difficult
Browse Category Meat, Rice & Pastas
Duration 15-30 min
Cooking Technique Pressure Cook
Main Ingredient Chicken Breast, Chicken Broth, Taco Seasoning
Keyword burrito bowl, chicken bowl, chicken dinner, chicken recipe, insta pot chicken, instant pot, instant pot chicken dinner recipe, instant pot chicken recipe, instant pot recipe
Prep Time 5 minutes
Cook Time 20 minutes
Servings
4-6 servings
Ingredients
Pot Mixture:
  • 2.25 cups chicken broth
  • 1.5 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts (if large, cut in half)
  • 1.25 ounces taco seasoning 1 packet
  • 1.5 cups long grain white rice rinsed
  • 12 ounce frozen corn kernels
  • 15 ounce black beans 1 can , drained and rinsed
  • 1 cup salsa
For Serving:
  • sour cream
  • diced tomatoes
  • shredded mexican blend cheese
  • Diced avocado

Cook Time 20 minutes
Servings
4-6 servings
Ingredients
Pot Mixture:
  • 2.25 cups chicken broth
  • 1.5 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts (if large, cut in half)
  • 1.25 ounces taco seasoning 1 packet
  • 1.5 cups long grain white rice rinsed
  • 12 ounce frozen corn kernels
  • 15 ounce black beans 1 can , drained and rinsed
  • 1 cup salsa
For Serving:
  • sour cream
  • diced tomatoes
  • shredded mexican blend cheese
  • Diced avocado
Votes: 190
Rating: 4.35
Rate this recipe!
Instructions
  1. Add the Pot Mixture ingredients to the Instant Pot, in the order listed.
  2. Secure the lid, making sure the vent is closed.
  3. Using the display panel select the MANUAL function*. Use the +/- keys and program the Instant Pot for 12 minutes.
  4. When the time is up, quick-release the remaining pressure.
  5. Carefully remove the chicken from the pot to a cutting board and shred, then return to the pot and stir.
  6. Serve in a bowl topped with sour cream, diced tomatoes, shredded Mexican-blend cheese and diced avocados.
Recipe Notes

*The MANUAL and PRESSURE COOK buttons are interchangeable.

    Hi Bgronitz,

    This recipe can cause a burn message if you do not layer the ingredients in the order they appear.

    When you have a burn error, release the steam and add in more liquid. You will also have to scrape the bottom of the inner pot, if there is any stuck on bits left stuck it will show burn again.

  110. Aaron says:
    February 24, 2019 at 11:51 pm

    This recipe has been my nemesis for two months. Tonight I FINALLY was able to not get a BURN message. For anyone else struggling, here’s what I did different this time.

    1. I cut the chicken longways so it covers the majority of the bottom.

    2. I measured and weighed EVERYTHING. Normally I eyeball ingredients but I used a food scale and measuring cups for every single item.

    3. Instead of dumping everything in, I gently poured each item in the center only and used a hand to flatten it out. I tried to carefully let the rice rest on top of the chicken, flatten, slowly pour corn on, etc.

    4. I didn’t move my IP once set. I usually slide it back so I have more counter space but I let it be this time so nothing could shift.

    I don’t know why this recipe is so difficult but I was finally able to conquer it by slowing down and being very careful and methodical. You can’t finagle this one. And in case it matters, I have the 6qt model.

    I hope this helps anyone in a similar situation.

  132. Instant Pot says:
    April 16, 2019 at 4:03 pm

    Hi mom2jpdcl,

    We are sorry to hear that this recipe didn’t work out. Before making any of our recipes, we recommend looking at the difficulty level. The cooking level for this recipe is difficult since it is very precise. All of the ingredients have to be added in the order they are listed. When you add the chicken broth you want to add it quickly with this recipe. Otherwise, some of the liquid will start to evaporate. Before restarting, remember to always de-glaze your Instant Pot Pressure Cooker, using a wooden spoon. If the unit was restarted without being de-glazed, more starch would be released. Unfortunately, this would cause it to burn more.
